<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="109" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.13902" author="Purcell, WF" journalOrPublisher="Annals of South African Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="131 - 180" refId="B147" refString="Purcell, WF, 1899. On the species of Opisthophthalmus in the collection of the South African Museum, with description of some new forms. Annals of South African Museum 1: 131 - 180" title="On the species of Opisthophthalmus in the collection of the South African Museum, with description of some new forms." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.13902" volume="1" year="1899">Purcell (1899</bibRefCitation>
: 149-150) considered 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. fuscipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="fuscipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">O. fuscipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Opistophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Opistophthalmus capensis" order="Scorpiones" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Opistophthalmus capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Herbst, 1800). 
<bibRefCitation author="Prendini, L" journalOrPublisher="African Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="17 - 48" refId="B144" refString="Prendini, L, 2001. A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae). African Entomology 9: 17 - 48" title="A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae)." volume="9" year="2001">Prendini (2001)</bibRefCitation>
subsequently highlighted consistent diagnostic differences between the two taxa and thus reinstated 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. fuscipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="fuscipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">O. fuscipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Prendini, L" journalOrPublisher="African Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="17 - 48" refId="B144" refString="Prendini, L, 2001. A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae). African Entomology 9: 17 - 48" title="A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae)." volume="9" year="2001">Prendini (2001)</bibRefCitation>
also designated lectotype and paralectotype from the syntype series housed in the SAMC collection but did not cite the present specimens. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.13904" author="Purcell, WF" journalOrPublisher="Annals of South African Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="1 - 32" refId="B146" refString="Purcell, WF, 1898. Description of new South African scorpions in the collection of the South African Museum. Annals of South African Museum 1: 1 - 32" title="Description of new South African scorpions in the collection of the South African Museum." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.13904" volume="1" year="1898">Purcell (1898)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that numerous specimens were part of the type series without giving a precise number. Given that the data of the present specimens match that of the original description, they are considered as paralectotypes.
</paragraph>
